The problem arises when I excecute the `update-package` command for my library. Besides the fact that it ignores the specifed version range (which is already covered [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49398602/constrain-packagereference-upgrade-version-when-update-package-run/)) it also overwrites the version range to the exact version number thus losing the range, i.e. instead of `Version=[8.0, 9.0)` it becomes `Version=&quot;11.0.1&quot;` (or would have become `Version=&quot;8.0.3&quot;` if it worked correctly and didn&#39;t ignore the upper limit, thus making the versions 8.0.1 and 8.0.2 unusable). 

